ue to the reduced dimensionality and interlayer coupling, CrSBr\nhosts spectrally narrow (1 meV) excitons of high binding energy and oscillator\nstrength that inherit the 1D character. Overall, CrSBr is best understood as a\nstack of weakly hybridized monolayers and appears to be an experimentally\nattractive candidate for the study of exotic exciton and 1D correlated\nmany-body physics in the presence of magnetic order.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 May 2022 16:03:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 2 Mar 2023 15:38:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-23"}
